[
    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "An abstraction is a model or representation that omits some details so that it can focus on other details.",
        "citations": [
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "An abstraction is a model or representation that omits some details so that it can focus on other details.",
                "img_id": null
            }
        ],
        "type": null
    },
    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "Different abstractions, built for different purposes, omit different kinds of details.",
        "citations": [
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "The definition is vague about which details are left out of a model, because different abstractions, built for different purposes, omit different kinds of details.",
                "img_id": null
            }
        ],
        "type": null
    },
    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "Abstraction involves identifying classes of objects that allow us to group items together, so we can deal with fewer things and concentrate on the commonalities of the items in each class.",
        "citations": [
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "Typically, abstraction involves identifying classes of objects that allow us to group items together; this way, we can deal with fewer things and concentrate on the commonalities of the items in each class.",
                "img_id": null
            }
        ],
        "type": null
    },
    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "Abstraction helps to simplify the problem statement and focus on the essential elements or characteristics of the problem by hiding some of the details.",
        "citations": [
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "By hiding some of the details, we can concentrate on the essential nature of the objects with which we must deal and derive solutions that are simple and elegant.",
                "img_id": null
            }
        ],
        "type": null
    },
    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "A fourth type of abstraction is the virtual machine, such as that in a layered architecture, where each layer abstracts away the details of the lower-level layers and presents only its services to the next layer.",
        "citations": [
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "A fourth type of abstraction is the virtual machine, such as that in a layered architecture. Each layer i in the architecture uses the services provided by the layer i -1 below it, to create more powerful and reliable services, which it then offers to the layer i + 1 above it. ... As such, layer i is a virtual machine that abstracts away the details of the lower-level layers and presents only its services to the next layer.",
                "img_id": null
            }
        ],
        "type": null
    }
]

