[
    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "Prototyping in the context of user interface prototyping means building a small version of a system, usually with limited functionality, that can be used to help the user or customer identify the key requirements of a system and demonstrate the feasibility of a design or approach.",
        "citations": [
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "User Interface Prototyping. Prototyping means building a small version of a system, usually with limited functionality, that can be used to Often, the prototyping process is iterative: We build a prototype, evaluate it (with user and customer feedback), consider how changes might improve the product or design, and then build another prototype.",
                "img_id": null
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "role": "sentence",
        "segment": "It is often used to design a good user interface, which is the part of the system with which the user interacts",
        "citations": [
