[
    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "The critical path is the longest path in the project for which the slack at every node is zero.",
        "citations": [
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "The longest path has a slack of zero for each of its nodes, because it is the path that determines whether or not the project is on schedule. For this reason, it is called the critical path.",
                "img_id": null
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "In the activity graph shown in Figure 3.23, the critical path can be identified by calculating the earliest start time, latest start time, and slack for each activity and selecting the path where slack is zero for all nodes.",
        "citations": [
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "Figure 3.23 is an activity graph for a software development project. The number corresponding to each edge of the graph indicates the number of days required to complete the activity represented by that branch. For each activity, list its precursors and compute the earliest start time, the latest start time, and the slack.Then, identify the critical path.",
                "img_id": null
            },
            {
                "type": "img",
