            }
        ],
        "type": null
    },
    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "In contrast, a UML Statechart diagram shows the local variables and internal activities of a single entity by depicting states and actions as labeled rectangles positioned on an entity's execution line, representing invoked operations or changes to variable values at specific points in the trace.",
        "citations": [
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "Actions , such as invoked operations or changes to variable values, are specified as labeled rectangles positioned on an entity's execution line, located at the point in the trace where the action occurs.",
